Reading this 4+ years after it came out, I wondered whether this or Good As New came out first. When I realized that it was the latter, I was disappointed that it appeared we were getting a retread of the same basic idea (although  becomes much funnier if you imagine it as polar opposite, rather than opposite direction within the socket).

When I got to the video log, I was pleasantly surprised to find that the overall plot of AR1 being moved forward, as the seemingly invincible organization begins to crumble from within. The two letters, particularly Anderson's lack of a closing beyond a signature, were quite well done. It was impressive that none of the characters came across as one-dimensional, even within the constraints of a video log/letter. Since I can't be positive, I will say that the  line felt a bit trite. Otherwise, though, outstanding work.



Vincent can always find another glorified accountant. But he only has one of me.
